{{one source|date=June 2011}} {{Taxobox <!-- Color parameter is not needed -- automatically assigned --> | name = Adelaide River virus (ARV) | virus_group = v | ordo = ''[[Mononegavirales]]'' | familia = ''[[Rhabdoviridae]]'' | genus = ''[[Ephemerovirus]]'' | species = ''Adelaide River ephemerovirus'' }}
'''Adelaide River virus''' is a [[Sense (molecular biology)|negative-sense]] [[single-stranded RNA]] virus of the family ''[[Rhabdoviridae]]''. The virus's primary hosts are all [[bovine]], including [[Bubalus bubalis|domestic Water Buffalo]], and [[Syncerus caffer|cape buffalo]].
