[[Image:Planarian12345.JPG|right|thumb|Freshwater planaria of the Karaj River under stones in the river.]] [[Image:River123456.JPG|right|thumb|Karaj River in central [[Alborz]].]] '''Behzad Ghorbani''' ( March 26, 1971, [[Tehran]]) is an [[Iran]]ian [[zoologist]] and the first Iranian [[Planarium|planarialogist]]. He graduated from the [[University of Tehran]] and [[Shahid Beheshti University]] (The National University of Iran). In 1997, he identified two new [[species]] (''Dugesia iranica'' and ''Dugesia persica''), that were found in the [[Karaj River]].
