'''Han Nijssen''' (1935– 2013)<ref name=aa>[http://www.albumacademicum.uva.nl/cgi/b/bib/bib-idx?type=boolean;lang=nl;searchtype=phd;c=ap;q1=nijssen;rgn1=entirerecord;op2=And;rgn2=entirerecord;op3=And;rgn3=entirerecord;op4=And;rgn4=entirerecord;date1=1576;date2=1992;date61=1634;date62=2016;cc=ap;view=reslist;sort=achternaam;fmt=long;page=reslist;start=1;size=1 H. Nijssen, 1935 -] at the UvA Album academicum</ref><ref>[http://www.ncrz.nl/pdf/Jaarverslag-1-2013.pdf Obituary] in the Nederlandse commissie record zeevissen (Ncrz) annual report for 2013</ref> was a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] [[ichthyologist]].<ref>DEPARTMENT of ICHTHYOLOGY California Academy of Sciences, Newsletter of Systematic Ichthyology Number Twenty-Two</ref>
Nijssen was born in [[Amsterdam]] and obtained his PhD at the [[University of Amsterdam]] in May 1970 with the dissertation ''Revision of the Surinam catfishes of the genus Corydoras''.<ref name=aa/> Later he was a [[curator]] at [[Zoölogisch Museum]] in [[Amsterdam]]. Nijssen worked extensively with [[fish]] from [[South America]], and was the [[Author citation (zoology)|author]] of several species, e.g. ''[[Corydoras weitzmani]]'' and ''[[Corydoras xinguensis]]''. Collaborating with [[Isaäc Isbrücker]] he described, among others, the group ''[[Hypancistrus]]'' and the species ''[[Hypancistrus zebra]]'' and ''[[Corydoras panda]]''. He also collaborated with [[Sven O. Kullander]].
The species ''[[Corydoras nijsseni]]'' and ''[[Apistogramma nijsseni]]''<ref>[http://www2.nrm.se/ve/pisces/acara/ap_nijss.shtml ''Apistogramma nijsseni'' Kullander] - [[Naturhistoriska riksmuseet]]</ref> are named after him.
==Publications (incomplete)== * Han Nijssen & S.J. de Groot, ''De vissen van Nederland.'' (1987) * Sven O. Kullander & Han Nijssen, ''The Cichlids of Surinam: Teleostei: Labroidei'' (1989) * Han Nijssen, ''Veldgids Zeevissen'' ("Field guide for saltwater fish"), KNNV 2009, {{ISBN|9789050111393}}
