{{Expand Portuguese|Albert Löfgren|date=November 2011}}{{ Infobox scientist | name = Johan Albert Constantin Löfgren | birth_date = 1854 | birth_place = | death_date = 1918 | death_place = | residence = | citizenship = | nationality = | ethnicity = | fields = [[botany]] | workplaces = | alma_mater = | doctoral_advisor = | academic_advisors = | doctoral_students = | notable_students = | known_for = | author_abbrev_bot = Loefgr. | author_abbrev_zoo = | influences = | influenced = | awards = | signature = <!--(filename only)--> | signature_alt = | footnotes = }} '''Johan Albert Constantin Löfgren''' (1854–1918), known as '''Albert Löfgren''' or '''Alberto Löfgren''', was head of the botany department of the [[Rio de Janeiro Botanical Garden]] around 1905. The plant currently known as ''[[Schlumbergera opuntioides]]'' is one of those he first named.<ref>{{Citation |last=McMillan |first=A.J.S. |last2=Horobin |first2=J.F. |year=1995 |title=Christmas Cacti : The genus ''Schlumbergera'' and its hybrids |edition=p/b |publication-place=Sherbourne, Dorset |publisher=David Hunt |isbn=978-0-9517234-6-3 }}, p. 14</ref>
Löfgren was the first director of the Horto Florestal de São Paulo, from 1907 to 1909, now named the [[Albert Löfgren State Park]].<ref>{{citation|ref={{harvid|Horto Florestal de São Paulo ... Áreas Verdes}}|language=pt |title=Horto Florestal de São Paulo ou Parque Estadual Albert Löfgren|date=21 June 2012|work=Áreas Verdes das Cidades |url=http://www.areasverdesdascidades.com.br/2012/06/parque-estadual-alfredo-lofgren-antigo.html|accessdate=2016-12-09}}</ref>
