==Applied physics== ===Accelerator physics=== {{Main|Accelerator physics}}
*{{cite journal |last=Ising |first=G. |authorlink=Gustav Ising |year=1924 |title=Prinzip einer Methode zur Herstellung von Kanalstrahlen hoher Voltzahl |language=German |journal=[[Arkiv för matematik, astronomi och fysik]] |volume=18 |issue=30 |pages=1–4 |doi= }} :The Swedish physicist [[Gustav Ising]] was the first one to publish the basic concept of a [[linear accelerator]] (in this case, as part of a cathode ray tube). *{{cite journal |last=Widerøe |first=R. |authorlink=Rolf Widerøe |year=1928 |title=Über ein neues Prinzip zur Herstellung hoher Spannungen |language=German |journal=[[Archiv für Elektrotechnik]] |volume=21 |issue=4 |pages=387–406 |doi=10.1007/BF01656341 }} :The Norwegian physicist [[Rolf Widerøe]] took Ising's idea and expanded it. Later, he built the first operational [[linear accelerator]]. *{{Cite journal |last1=Kerst |first1=D. W. |authorlink=Donald William Kerst |year=1941 |title=The Acceleration of Electrons by Magnetic Induction |url=http://web.ihep.su/dbserv/compas/src/kerst41/eng.pdf |journal=[[Physical Review]] |volume=60 |issue=1 |pages=47–53 |bibcode=1941PhRv...60...47K |doi=10.1103/PhysRev.60.47 }} *{{Cite journal |last1=Kerst |first1=D. W. |authorlink1=Donald William Kerst |last2=Serber |first2=R. |authorlink2=Robert Serber |year=1941 |title=Electronic Orbits in the Induction Accelerator |journal=[[Physical Review]] |volume=60 |issue=1 |pages=53–58 |bibcode=1941PhRv...60...53K |doi=10.1103/PhysRev.60.53 }} :These two articles describe the [[betatron]] concept and the first experimental data of a working betatron, built by [[Donald William Kerst]]. *{{Cite journal |last1=Courant |first1=E. D. |authorlink1=Ernest Courant |last2=Livingston |first2=M. S. |authorlink2=M. Stanley Livingston |last3=Snyder |first3=H. S. |authorlink3=Hartland Snyder |year=1952 |title=The Strong-Focusing Synchrotron—A New High Energy Accelerator |journal=[[Physical Review]] |volume=88 |issue=5 |pages=1190–1196 |bibcode=1952PhRv...88.1190C |doi=10.1103/PhysRev.88.1190 |hdl=2027/mdp.39015086454124 }} *{{cite journal |last1=Courant |first1=E. D. |authorlink1=Ernest Courant |last2=Snyder |first2=H. S. |authorlink2=Hartland Snyder |year=1958 |title=Theory of the alternating-gradient synchrotron |url=http://ab-abp-rlc.web.cern.ch/ab-abp-rlc/AP-literature/Courant-Snyder-1958.pdf |journal=[[Annals of Physics]] |volume=3 |issue=1 |pages=1–48 |bibcode=2000AnPhy.281..360C |doi=10.1006/aphy.2000.6012 }} :These publications were the first to introduce the idea of [[strong focusing]] to [[particle beam]]s, enabling the transition from compact circular accelerator concepts to separate-function magnet devices like [[synchrotron]]s, [[storage ring]]s and [[particle collider]]s.
