===Geophysics=== {{See also|Geophysics|History of geophysics}}
*{{cite book |last=Gilbert |first=W. |authorlink=William Gilbert (astronomer) |year=1600 |title=De Magnete, Magneticisque Corporibus, et de Magno Magnete Tellure |trans-title=On the Magnet and Magnetic Bodies, and on That Great Magnet the Earth |language=Latin |publisher=[[Peter Short (printer)|Peter Short]] |title-link=De Magnete }} **English translation: {{cite book |last=Gilbert |first=W. |title=De Magnete |year=1991 |publisher=[[Dover Publications]] |isbn=978-0-486-26761-6 }} Republication of the 1893 unabridged and unaltered translation by Paul Fleury Mottelay. :Early description of magnetism from an Elizabethan scientist consisting of six books. Erroneously attributes magnetism as causing the motion of bodies in the Solar system.<ref>{{cite book|title=Physical Sciences, Encyclopædia Britannica: Macropaedia|year=1994|page=831|title-link=Encyclopædia Britannica}}</ref> *{{cite book |last=Chapman |first=S. |author-link=Sydney Chapman (mathematician) |last2=Bartels |first2=J. |author2-link=Julius Bartels |year=1940 |title=Geomagnetism Volume 1: Geomagnetic and Related Phenomena |url=https://archive.org/details/GeomagnetismVol1 |publisher=[[Clarendon Press]] |asin=B002K07MAO |oclc=499431969 }} *{{cite book |last=Chapman |first=S. |author-link=Sydney Chapman (mathematician) |last2=Bartels |first2=J. |author2-link=Julius Bartels |year=1940 |title=Geomagnetism Volume 2: Analysis of the Data and Physical Theories |url=https://archive.org/details/GeomagnetismVol2 |publisher=[[Clarendon Press]] |asin=B0020TCMR8 |oclc=458641769 }} :A classic reference on the Earth's magnetic field and related topics in [[meteorology]], [[Solar physics|solar]] and [[Moon|lunar]] physics, the [[Aurora (astronomy)|aurora]], techniques of [[Spherical harmonics|spherical harmonic analysis]] and treatment of periodicities in geophysical data.<ref> {{cite web |title = Awards & Medals: Julius Bartels |url = http://www.egu.eu/awards-medals/award/portrait-julius-bartels.html |archive-url = https://archive.is/20120728162017/http://www.egu.eu/awards-medals/award/portrait-julius-bartels.html |dead-url = yes |archive-date = 2012-07-28 |publisher = [[European Geosciences Union]] |accessdate = 30 September 2011 }}</ref> Its comprehensive summaries made it the standard reference on [[geomagnetism]] and the [[ionosphere]] for at least 2 decades.<ref> {{cite journal |last1=Akasofu |first1=S.-I. |year=2011 |title=The Scientific Legacy of Sydney Chapman |journal=[[Eos (journal)|EOS]] |volume=92 |issue=34 |pages=281&ndash;282 |bibcode=2011EOSTr..92..281A |doi=10.1029/2011EO340001 }}</ref> *{{cite book |last=Yilmaz |first=Ö. |year=1999 |title=Seismic data processing |edition=9th |publisher=[[Society of Exploration Geophysicists]] |isbn=978-0-931830-40-2 }} :Up to date account of seismic data processing in the petroleum geophysics industry.{{citation needed|date=November 2011}}
