[[File:Boojum Tree.jpg|thumb|right|''Fouquieria columnaris'']] '''Pachycauls''' are [[plant]]s with a disproportionately thick [[Trunk (botany)|trunk]] for their height, and few branches.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=TXmOcFArNDkC&q=pachycaul#v=snippet&q=pachycaul&f=false |title=Concepts' Dictionary Of Agricultural Sciences |first=I. C. |last=Gupta |author2=S. K. Gupta |publisher=Concept Publishing Company |year=1992 |isbn=978-81-7022-301-6 |page=348}}</ref> The word is derived from the [[Greek language|Greek]] ''pachy-'' meaning thick or stout, and [[Latin language|Latin]] ''caulis'' meaning the stem.<ref>{{cite book|author=Stearn, W.T.|year=1992|title=Botanical Latin: History, grammar, syntax, terminology and vocabulary, Fourth edition|publisher=David and Charles}}</ref>
Examples occur in the genera<ref>{{cite book |title=The Baobabs: Pachycauls of Africa, Madagascar and Australia |first=G. E. |last=Wickens |author2=Pat Lowe |year=2008 |publisher=Springer |isbn=978-1-4020-6430-2 |pages=139–140}}</ref> *''[[Pachycormus (plant)|Pachycormus]]'' ([[Anacardiaceae]]) *''[[Adenium]]'' *''[[Pachypodium]]'' ([[Apocynaceae]]) *''[[Dendrosenecio]]'' ([[Asteraceae]]) *''[[Bursera]]'' ([[Burseraceae]]) *''[[Cyanea (plant)|Cyanea]]'' *''[[Lobelia]]'' ([[Campanulaceae]]) *''[[Dendrosicyos]]'' ([[Cucurbitaceae]]) *''[[Givotia]]'' ([[Euphorbiaceae]]) *''[[Delonix]]'' ([[Fabaceae]]) *''[[Fouquieria]]'' ([[Fouquieriaceae]]) *''[[Adansonia]]'' *''[[Bombax]]'' *''[[Brachychiton]]'' *''[[Cavanillesia]]'' *''[[Ceiba]]'' ([[Malvaceae]]) *''[[Dorstenia]]'' ([[Moraceae]]) *''[[Cyphostemma]]'' ([[Vitaceae]]).
